Paper: hep-th/9304012

Date: 1993-04-05

Title: General Form of Dilaton Gravity and Nonlinear Gauge Theory

Authors: Noriaki Ikeda and Izawa K.-I

Comments: 12 pages, phyzzx, RIMS-918

Journal-ref: Prog.Theor.Phys. 90 (1993) 237-246

We construct a gauge theory based on general nonlinear Lie algebras. Thegeneric form of `dilaton' gravity is derived from nonlinear Poincar{\' e}algebra, which exhibits a gauge-theoretical origin of the non-geometric scalarfield in two-dimensional gravitation theory.